channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Cats head into destination unknown
item.description: Geelong left Optus Stadium after Thursday night’s dominant win over Fremantle on top of the ladder but with no clarity on where they would play their round 19 clash with Richmond.

item.title: Teen stabbed at Melbourne supermarket
item.description: A teenager is fighting for life after a stabbing at a supermarket in Melbourne’s northern suburbs on Thursday night.

item.title: At least 68 dead in Germany, Belgium as storms ravage Europe
item.description: Heavy rains and floods lashing western Europe have killed at least 59 people in Germany and nine in Belgium, and many more people are missing as rising waters caused several houses to collapse on Thursday.

item.title: Victoria records 6 new local virus cases
item.description: Victoria has recorded six new locally acquired Covid-19 cases on Friday.

item.title: Palaszczuk still planning Tokyo trip
item.description: Annastacia Palaszczuk will fly out to Tokyo on Sunday ahead of the Olympic Games, but the Premier insists she would cancel the trip if Queensland was plunged into a Covid-19 emergency “like NSW”.

item.title: KFC joins surging Victorian alerts list
item.description: A KFC restaurant and a Chemist Warehouse have been added to a surging list of public exposure sites in Victoria.

item.title: Busy Brisbane chemist on Covid alert
item.description: Health authorities are scrambling to trace contacts and test those exposed to new Covid-19 infections recorded in Queensland.

item.title: Fears of new Sydney superspreading event
item.description: The list of potential exposure sites in NSW has expanded further, as contact tracers rush to keep up with the rapidly spreading coronavirus outbreak in Sydney.

item.title: Coles, Woolies bring back purchase limits
item.description: The threat of panic buying has prompted the nation’s major supermarkets to reinstate purchase limits in Victoria as the state enters a record fifth lockdown.

item.title: ‘Kick in the guts’: Furious Vic unleashes
item.description: Victorians are waking up to a new, five-day lockdown after Sydney's disastrous covid outbreak spilled over the border.
